  {
    "id": "ch_mndqkdko66klp",
    "text": "March Madness is here—but I’m looking at a different kind of bracket this year 🏀🎓\n\nI’m sharing this “financial bracket” from Columbia Threadneedle that breaks down the real cost of a 4-year college degree, including tuition, room, board and the numbers might surprise you.\n\n🏆 Vanderbilt takes the championship at $376,568\n🥈 Miami follows closely at $375,568\n🥉 Duke comes in at $362,784\n\nNow imagine what these costs could look like in 18 years if you have a newborn today…\n\nAs college costs continue to climb, the takeaway is simple: the earlier you start planning, the better positioned you’ll be.\n\nIf paying for education is part of your financial goals, now is a great time to put a strategy in place. Let’s connect and start building a college savings plan that works for your family.\n\n#MarchMadness #CollegeCosts #FinancialPlanning #529Plan #EducationSavings",
